    "body": "cc https://github.com/KMiri-rs/KMiri/issues/75\n\n`invoke_ffi_init_funcs` currently depends on linker-defined symbols (`__sinit_array`, `__einit_array`) and link/assembly layout assumptions. KMiri cannot model this path directly today, so we skip it under `kmiri`.\n\nIf we want first-class support, KMiri should provide an explicit shim-based model for \"FFI init arrays\" instead of relying on raw symbol arithmetic.\n\n## Proposed direction\n\n### 1. Add a KMiri init-registry abstraction\nIntroduce a runtime registry in KMiri that represents init routines to be called at boot:\n\n- ordered list of function entries\n- stable call order semantics\n- optional metadata (component name, priority)\n\nThis replaces scanning `__sinit_array..__einit_array` memory directly.\n\n### 2. Add dedicated foreign-symbol shims for init boundaries\nProvide controlled handling for symbols such as:\n\n- `__sinit_array`\n- `__einit_array`\n\nInstead of treating them as unknown foreign symbols, KMiri should map them to shim-backed addresses that represent the registry boundaries.\n\n### 3. Add an API/shim to iterate or invoke init entries\nTwo possible interfaces:\n\n- pointer-compatible mode: emulate boundary symbols and a contiguous function-pointer view\n- explicit mode: provide a KMiri intrinsic/shim like `kmiri_invoke_init_funcs()`\n\nExplicit mode is easier to keep sound and debug.\n\n### 4. Define clear semantics for unsupported entries\nIf an init entry is invalid or unsupported:\n\n- emit a dedicated KMiri diagnostic\n- include entry index/name when available\n- fail fast (do not continue with partially initialized state)\n\n### 5. Keep strict default behavior\nUnknown external symbols should still be rejected by default.\nOnly a small whitelist for init-array symbols should be shimmed.\n\n## Minimal implementation plan\n\n1. Add `InitRegistry` in KMiri machine state.\n2. Populate registry from known boot/component metadata (or a fixed list for initial prototype).\n3. Shim `__sinit_array`/`__einit_array` resolution to synthetic addresses tied to registry storage.\n4. Ensure function-pointer loads/calls from that range dispatch to registered Rust instances.\n5. Add tests:\n   - successful init iteration and call order\n   - empty init array\n   - invalid entry diagnostic\n   - unknown symbol still rejected outside whitelist.\n\n## Expected outcome\n\nWith these shims, KMiri can execute `invoke_ffi_init_funcs` meaningfully, while preserving soundness and avoiding linker-layout-dependent behavior.",
